THAT YOU RESCUED HIM

239
00:33:39,434 --> 00:33:41,829
BECAUSE I DIDN'T
BELIEVE IN YOU.

240
00:33:44,506 --> 00:33:47,673
WHEN YOU DIED, I DIDN'T
BELIEVE IN THE IDEA OF YOU.

241
00:33:47,706 --> 00:33:49,374
IT'S OKAY, LUKE.

242
00:33:49,407 --> 00:33:51,906
I DIDN'T COME HERE
TO MAKE YOU BELIEVE IN ME.

243
00:33:51,940 --> 00:33:53,798
I CAME HERE
TO MAKE YOU BELIEVE IN YOU.

244
00:33:56,670 --> 00:33:57,641
YOU KNOW...

245
00:33:57,642 --> 00:34:00,407
YOU GOT A LOT OF GOOD THINGS
IN THIS LIFE, LUKE.

246
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:03,626
YOU GOT FAMILY,
FRIENDS, LOVE.

247
00:34:04,307 --> 00:34:06,417
THOSE ARE THE THINGS
THAT ARE WORTH BELIEVING IN.

248
00:34:14,374 --> 00:34:17,538
IS THERE A HEAVEN, KEITH?

249
00:34:19,522 --> 00:34:20,920
I DON'T KNOW. IS THERE?

250
00:34:22,307 --> 00:34:24,286
YOU KNOW,
YOU REALLY SUCK AT THIS.

251
00:34:28,273 --> 00:34:29,372
BECAUSE IF THERE IS,

252
00:34:29,773 --> 00:34:32,437
I WAS KIND OF WONDERING
IF I COULD GO WITH YOU.

253
00:34:33,792 --> 00:34:35,554
WELL, LUKE,
THAT'S UP TO YOU.

254
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:38,977
THE FUTURE RIGHT NOW
IS UNWRITTEN.

255
00:34:39,802 --> 00:34:41,486
BUT I WANT YOU
TO UNDERSTAND --

256
00:34:43,087 --> 00:34:43,705
IF YOU GO BACK,

257
00:34:43,706 --> 00:34:46,040
THERE ARE GONNA BE TOUGH TIMES,
YOU KNOW?

258
00:34:46,073 --> 00:34:47,706
SOME HEARTACHE
AND PAIN.

259
00:34:47,740 --> 00:34:50,073
BUT THERE'S ALSO GONNA BE
LOVE, LAUGHTER,

260
00:34:50,107 --> 00:34:52,273
AND A LIFE
FULL OF ACCOMPLISHMENT.

261
00:34:52,307 --> 00:34:53,574
IT'S UP TO YOU.

262
00:34:58,539 --> 00:35:00,490
WHO'S THE WOMAN
AT PEYTON'S GRAVE?

263
00:35:00,806 --> 00:35:03,348
SOMEONE WHO USED TO
KNOW HER.

264
00:35:04,711 --> 00:35:06,498
BUT IT'S NOT
PEYTON'S GRAVE.

265
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:09,173
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

266
00:35:09,207 --> 00:35:12,209
WELL, PEYTON LIVED
BECAUSE YOU SAVED HER THAT DAY.

267
00:35:13,649 --> 00:35:16,840
THEN WHOSE GRAVE IS IT?

268
00:35:16,873 --> 00:35:21,773
IT'S YOUR GRAVE, LUKE,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU CHOOSE.

269
00:35:34,130 --> 00:35:36,080
AND THE WOMAN?

270
00:35:43,573 --> 00:35:45,317
PEYTON.

271
00:35:46,474 --> 00:35:48,146
SHE LIVED
A GOOD LIFE, LUKE.

272
00:35:49,454 --> 00:35:51,333
BUT SHE COULD NEVER
LET GO OF YOU.

273
00:36:13,654 --> 00:36:15,333
I HAVE TO GO BACK.

274
00:36:17,190 --> 00:36:18,246
[ CHUCKLES ]

275
00:36:19,044 --> 00:36:20,009
ARE YOU SURE?

276
00:36:21,553 --> 00:36:24,623
I NEVER TOLD PEYTON
I LOVE HER.

277
00:36:25,178 --> 00:36:26,970
I WANT TO GO BACK.

278
00:36:28,544 --> 00:36:30,219
OKAY.

279
00:36:31,344 --> 00:36:32,477
WELL...

280
00:36:34,415 --> 00:36:36,218
I GUESS
THIS IS THE HARD PART.

281
00:36:36,412 --> 00:36:37,998
KEITH...

282
00:36:37,998 --> 00:36:41,397
LUKE, YOU KNOW I LOVE YOU,
AND I ALWAYS WILL.

283
00:36:42,168 --> 00:36:44,132
BUT I'M AFRAID
IT'S TIME FOR ME TO GO.

284
00:36:44,635 --> 00:36:46,989
I DON'T WANT YOU TO GO.
LUKE, IT'S OKAY.

285
00:36:50,602 --> 00:36:54,510
GOD...I AM GONNA MISS YOU
SO MUCH.

286
00:36:55,335 --> 00:36:57,816
WHY?
I'M WITH YOU EVERY DAY.

287
00:37:00,201 --> 00:37:03,235
[ SNIFFLES ]

288
00:37:03,268 --> 00:37:04,922
I'M WITH YOU EVERY DAY.

289
00:37:11,168 --> 00:37:13,245
BESIDES
[CLEARS THROAT]

290
00:37:13,495 --> 00:37:15,041
WE'LL SEE
EACH OTHER AGAIN.

291
00:37:15,696 --> 00:37:17,296
WE WILL?

292
00:37:19,107 --> 00:37:20,862
YOU BELIEVE THAT.

293
00:37:24,807 --> 00:37:26,774
NOW, UH...

294
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:29,696
...THIS IS GONNA HURT
A LITTLE BIT.

295
00:37:30,826 --> 00:37:32,908
I LOVE YOU, KID.

296
00:37:44,558 --> 00:37:45,393
I GOT A HEARTBEAT.

297
00:37:49,924 --> 00:37:52,675
IT'S OKAY, LUCAS.
JUST BREATHE.

298
00:37:53,302 --> 00:37:55,062
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

299
00:37:57,799 --> 00:38:01,103
* DO-DO-DO DO-DO
DO-DO-DO DO-DO *

300
00:38:03,881 --> 00:38:07,180
* SHE BELONGS SOMEWHERE ELSE 

301
00:38:07,181 --> 00:38:10,714
* AWAY FROM MY SIDE 

302
00:38:10,747 --> 00:38:15,081
* SO RUN WITH WHAT YOU'VE GOT 

303
00:38:15,114 --> 00:38:18,881
* AND CHASE WITH WHAT YOU NEED 

304
00:38:18,914 --> 00:38:21,647
* I BELIEVE
THE FAITHFUL FAIL *

305
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,380
* DIDN'T KNOW IF THEY... 

306
00:38:23,413 --> 00:38:26,580
YOU UNDERSTAND THERE ARE
NO GUARANTEES IN MEDICINE,

307
00:38:26,614 --> 00:38:29,580
BUT AS LONG AS WE CAN LOCATE
A HEARTBEAT,

308
00:38:29,614 --> 00:38:31,147
THERE'S NO REASON TO EXPECT

309
00:38:31,181 --> 00:38:33,647
THAT THIS BABY WON'T BE
PERFECTLY HEALTHY.

310
00:38:33,680 --> 00:38:35,647
* IS IT MINE? 

311
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:37,647
* IS IT MINE? 

312
00:38:37,680 --> 00:38:40,780
[ HEARTBEAT ]

313
00:38:40,814 --> 00:38:43,947
[ LAUGHS ]

314
00:38:50,580 --> 00:38:54,114
* DO YOU TAKE
THE NON BELIEVER? *

315
00:38:54,147 --> 00:38:59,014
* DO-DO-DO DO-DO
DO-DO-DO DO-DO *

316
00:38:59,047 --> 00:39:01,747
* 'CAUSE I'M A NON BELIEVER 

317
00:39:01,780 --> 00:39:05,814
* DO-DO-DO DO-DO
-DO-DO DO-DO *

318
00:39:08,380 --> 00:39:11,647
Lucas: HAVE YOU EVER WONDERED
 WHAT MARKS OUR TIME HERE...

319
00:39:13,981 --> 00:39:16,881
 ...IF ONE LIFE CAN REALLY MAKE
 AN IMPACT ON THE WORLD...

320
00:39:20,248 --> 00:39:23,248
 ...OR IF THE CHOICES
 WE MAKE MATTER?

321
00:39:26,248 --> 00:39:27,566
 I BELIEVE THEY DO.

322
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:32,814
 AND I BELIEVE THAT ONE MAN
 CAN CHANGE MANY LIVES.

323
00:39:33,854 --> 00:39:36,180
 FOR BETTER...OR WORSE.

324
00:39:36,181 --> 00:39:39,647
I STILL DON'T BELIEVE
THAT JIMMY KILLED YOU, KEITH.

325
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:41,214
WELL, THEN WHY DO YOU?

326
00:39:41,248 --> 00:39:43,814
JIMMY EDWARDS
WAS YOUR FRIEND, LUKE.

327
00:39:43,847 --> 00:39:46,380
YOU KNEW HIM.
YOU WERE KIND TO HIM.

328
00:39:46,413 --> 00:39:48,181
AFTER EVERYTHING WE'VE SEEN,

329
00:39:48,214 --> 00:39:51,314
DON'T YOU THINK THAT
THAT KINDNESS HAD AN IMPACT?

330
00:39:51,348 --> 00:39:54,413
BUT IF IT DID,
THEN YOU WOULD STILL BE ALIVE.

331
00:39:54,447 --> 00:39:56,814
DO YOU REALLY
BELIEVE THAT, LUKE?

332
00:39:56,847 --> 00:39:58,647
LOOK INTO YOUR HEART, OKAY?

333
00:39:58,680 --> 00:40:01,747
IT MAY BE FLAWED PHYSICALLY,
BUT IT'S A GOOD ONE,

334
00:40:01,780 --> 00:40:03,647
AND IT'S WHAT
MAKES YOU YOU.

335
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:07,100
LOOK, YOU'VE CHANGED OTHER
PEOPLE'S LIVES BY OPENING IT UP.

336
00:40:07,214 --> 00:40:09,146
DON'T CLOSE THAT OFF.

337
00:40:10,380 --> 00:40:12,580
JUST LOOK AROUND
THIS HALLWAY.

338
00:40:12,614 --> 00:40:15,024
YOU WERE HERE THAT DAY.
WHAT DID YOU SEE?

339
00:40:15,447 --> 00:40:17,684
I DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.

340
00:40:17,847 --> 00:40:20,147
OPEN YOUR EYES, LUKE.

341
00:40:20,181 --> 00:40:24,714
OPEN YOUR EYES THE WAY
YOU'VE OPENED YOUR HEART.

342
00:40:24,747 --> 00:40:27,614
OPEN YOUR EYES, LUKE.

343
00:40:29,348 --> 00:40:32,248
OPEN YOUR EYES, LUKE.

344
00:40:32,281 --> 00:40:34,314
OPEN UP YOUR EYES, LUKE.

345
00:40:34,348 --> 00:40:36,714
JUST OPEN YOUR EYES, LUKE.

346
00:40:36,747 --> 00:40:39,447
OPEN YOUR EYES, LUCAS.

347
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:41,214
